Identity Management

Identity Schema

Identities are defined using YAML files with the following structure:

```yaml
# Required fields
identity_id: "uuid-string"
entity_type: "individual"  # or business, government_entity, etc.
verified_status:
  level: "verified"  # unverified, basic, verified, fully_verified, kyc_compliant
  last_verified: "2026-01-15T10:30:00Z"
metadata:
  created_at: "2026-01-15T10:30:00Z"

# Personal information (for individuals)
personal_info:
  legal_name:
    first_name: "John"
    last_name: "Doe"
  date_of_birth: "1980-01-15"
  place_of_birth:
    city: "Denver"
    state: "CO"
    country: "US"

# Contact information
contact_info:
  addresses:
    - type: "residential"
      street: "123 Main St"
      city: "Denver"
      state: "CO"
      country: "US"
      verified: true
  communication:
    email_addresses:
      - address: "john@example.com"
        verified: true
```